Sentencas: The electrochemical and crystalline structure of mixed ionic-electronic conductive La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.3Ni0.2O3-delta (LSCMN) electrode in porous scandia ceria stabilized zirconia (ScCeSZ) electrolyte matrix during the first 140 h has been studied in an operando XRD experiment.
Titulo: Study of Electrochemical and Crystallographic Changes During Initial Stabilization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.3Ni0.2O3-δ Reversible Solid Oxide Cell Electrode

Sentencas: Intense degradation of electrochemical performance in a fuel cell as well as in electrolysis modes has been observed.
Titulo: Study of Electrochemical and Crystallographic Changes During Initial Stabilization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.3Ni0.2O3-δ Reversible Solid Oxide Cell Electrode

Sentencas: However, the mechanism of the degradation was seen to be different for the two operation modes.
Titulo: Study of Electrochemical and Crystallographic Changes During Initial Stabilization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.3Ni0.2O3-δ Reversible Solid Oxide Cell Electrode

Sentencas: The formation of the new ceramic phase was observed on the surface of the electrode using the Grazing incidence X-ray diffraction at the pulsed laser deposited LSCMN model electrode.
Titulo: Study of Electrochemical and Crystallographic Changes During Initial Stabilization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.3Ni0.2O3-δ Reversible Solid Oxide Cell Electrode

Sentencas: Instability of the LSCMN phase in the ScCeSZ matrix at SOFC working conditions has been demonstrated using the novel operando XRD technique.
Titulo: Study of Electrochemical and Crystallographic Changes During Initial Stabilization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.3Ni0.2O3-δ Reversible Solid Oxide Cell Electrode

Sentencas: The decrease in wt.% of the LSCMN during degradation was approximately 27 +/- 4.5%.
Titulo: Study of Electrochemical and Crystallographic Changes During Initial Stabilization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.3Ni0.2O3-δ Reversible Solid Oxide Cell Electrode

Sentencas: A slow increase of the ScCeSZ lattice parameter was observed and attributed to the doping of electrolytes with some LSCMN components.
Titulo: Study of Electrochemical and Crystallographic Changes During Initial Stabilization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.3Ni0.2O3-δ Reversible Solid Oxide Cell Electrode
